# Invite And Auth Routing

- Canonical invite/deep-link route is `/join/:code`.
- Canonical public invite-link domain is `https://in-game.app`; native iOS/Android link verification should target that host.
- Browser app deployments may use a separate host such as `https://app.in-game.app`; do not assume the SPA host and invite-link host are the same.
- Keep `/groups/join/:code` only as a legacy redirect target; new links and navigation should point to `/join/:code`.
- If auth blocks a deep link, preserve the original destination in `from` and return there after successful login/register/Steam auth.
- Invite links should be shareable app/web URLs plus the raw invite code, not just a custom scheme string.
- When platform link verification is needed, keep the hosted `/.well-known/apple-app-site-association` and `/.well-known/assetlinks.json` aligned with the current bundle/package identifiers.
- Join screens should preview the target group before joining when backend metadata is available.
- After joining from an invite or discover flow, refresh the groups list/provider before navigating to group detail.
- Routing or user-flow changes here require matching updates in `docs/specs/2026-05-30-core-platform-design.md`.
